    <!-- Deck Ovens -->
    <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:1rem;">Deck Ovens</h2>
<img src="/images/convection-oven.jpg" alt="Convection Oven" class="product-img" loading="lazy">

    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Deck ovens are the gold standard for artisan breads, baguettes, and traditional bakery products. The stone or ceramic deck provides bottom heat that creates a perfect crust. In India, deck ovens are the most popular choice for bread-focused bakeries.</p>
    
    <div class="card-grid" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>1-Deck Deck Oven</h3>
<img src="/images/rotary-oven.jpg" alt="Rotary Oven" class="product-img" loading="lazy">

        <p>Single-deck entry-level oven. Ideal for small bakeries producing up to 30–50 loaves per hour.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹65,000 – ₹1,20,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Home bakers scaling up, small neighbourhood bakeries</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>2-Deck Deck Oven</h3>
<img src="/images/pizza-oven.jpg" alt="Pizza Oven" class="product-img" loading="lazy">

        <p>Two independent baking chambers. Doubles output while allowing different temperatures for different products.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹1,20,000 – ₹2,80,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Medium bakeries, artisan bread specialists</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>3-Deck Deck Oven</h3>
        <p>Three chambers with independent temperature controls. Standard setup for serious commercial bakeries.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹2,50,000 – ₹5,00,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: High-volume commercial bakeries</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>4-Deck Deck Oven</h3>
        <p>Maximum production in a single footprint. Used by large-scale commercial bakeries and industrial operations.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹4,50,000 – ₹9,00,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Industrial bakeries, large-scale production</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Convection Ovens -->
    <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:1rem;">Convection Ovens</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Convection ovens use a fan to circulate hot air, ensuring even heat distribution throughout the chamber. They're excellent for pastries, cakes, cookies, and anything that benefits from consistent browning. Convection ovens are more energy-efficient than deck ovens and heat up faster.</p>
    
    <div class="card-grid" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Small Convection Oven (4–6 tray)</h3>
        <p>Countertop or compact floor-standing models. Perfect for cafés, small bakeries, and pastry shops.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹35,000 – ₹85,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Cafés, small pastry shops, cloud kitchens</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Medium Convection Oven (8–10 tray)</h3>
        <p>The most popular size for Indian bakeries. Balances production capacity with kitchen footprint.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹85,000 – ₹1,80,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Medium bakeries, restaurants with in-house baking</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Large Convection Oven (16–20 tray)</h3>
        <p>High-capacity ovens for serious production. Can bake hundreds of pastries per hour.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹1,80,000 – ₹4,00,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: High-volume bakeries, hotel kitchens</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Rotary Rack Ovens -->
    <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:1rem;">Rotary Rack Ovens</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Rotary rack ovens are the workhorses of industrial bakeries. A full rack of trays rotates inside the oven chamber, ensuring every tray gets equal exposure to heat. One bake cycle can produce hundreds of loaves or thousands of pastries. These are big machines — you need ceiling height and floor space.</p>
    
    <div class="card-grid" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Half-Rack Rotary Oven</h3>
        <p>Smaller rotary design for medium-scale production. Accommodates 8–12 trays.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹3,50,000 – ₹6,00,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Scaling bakeries, QSR chains</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Full-Rack Rotary Oven</h3>
        <p>Full-production rotary rack with 16–24 trays. The standard for large commercial bakeries.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹6,00,000 – ₹14,00,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Industrial bakeries, large hotel chains</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Double-Rack Rotary Oven</h3>
        <p>Two racks rotating simultaneously for maximum production — industrial-grade equipment.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹12,00,000 – ₹25,00,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Industrial bakeries, large-scale food production</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Pizza Ovens -->
    <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:1rem;">Commercial Pizza Ovens</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Commercial pizza ovens are designed for the extreme temperatures (350–500°C) needed for authentic pizza. Whether you're running a pizzeria, a restaurant with a pizza menu, or a cloud kitchen, choosing the right pizza oven type is critical.</p>
    
    <div class="card-grid" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Electric Pizza Oven</h3>
        <p>Precise temperature control, easy to install (no gas line needed), and consistent results. Popular for cloud kitchens and restaurants.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹40,000 – ₹2,50,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Cloud kitchens, restaurants, indoor installation</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Gas Pizza Oven</h3>
        <p>Faster recovery time and lower running costs than electric. Preferred for high-volume pizza production.</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹60,000 – ₹3,50,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: High-volume pizzerias, restaurant chains</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Wood-Fired / Conveyor Pizza Oven</h3>
        <p>Wood-fired for authentic Neapolitan style; conveyor ovens for ultra-high volume chains (100+ pizzas per hour).</p>
        <div class="price-tag">₹1,20,000 – ₹8,00,000</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Artisan pizzerias, large chains</p>
      </div>
    </div>

